He conducted underground party work in the Far East among the local and Russian population, was repeatedly arrested for this. After the February Revolution of 1917, he was a member of the Council of Deputies of the Koryak region. Since March 1917, he was the chairman of the Koryak Committee of the Bolsheviks. Revolutionary activity

During the days of the Great October Socialist Revolution, in November 1917, he was the commissar of the Petrograd Military Revolutionary Committee (for city government). Together with F. E. Dzerzhinsky, he worked on organizing the All-Russian Extraordinary Commission (VChK).